\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Volterra-aware prototype (\ref {eq:volterra-surrogate}) vs the best spectral approach. Both use the same $z$-Cholesky correlation ($\rho =-0.9$). The V-conditional diffusion ($\sqrt  {V_j}$ in the noise term) is the architectural element that closes the cross-model bias.}}{8}{table.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:volterra-prototype}{{8}{8}{Volterra-aware prototype (\ref {eq:volterra-surrogate}) vs the best spectral approach. Both use the same $z$-Cholesky correlation ($\rho =-0.9$). The V-conditional diffusion ($\sqrt {V_j}$ in the noise term) is the architectural element that closes the cross-model bias}{table.8}{}}
