\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces End-to-end training of the Volterra surrogate from misspecified init $(\theta , \kappa , \nu ) = (0.10, 1.0, 0.5)$. The auxiliary V-moment loss resolves price-only identifiability and produces the first \emph  {trained} surrogate to beat the spectral floor.}}{8}{table.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:volterra-trained}{{9}{8}{End-to-end training of the Volterra surrogate from misspecified init $(\theta , \kappa , \nu ) = (0.10, 1.0, 0.5)$. The auxiliary V-moment loss resolves price-only identifiability and produces the first \emph {trained} surrogate to beat the spectral floor}{table.9}{}}
