\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces Sub-quadratic Volterra via $M$-mode RL kernel approximation ($H=0.1$, $N=252$, batch $5\,000$, GPU). $M = 5$ already saturates the kernel-fit error ($\approx 4\%$ relative) and gives the best IV-RMSE of the sweep, $7\times $ faster than the exact $O(N^2)$ baseline.}}{9}{table.10}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:markov-volterra}{{10}{9}{Sub-quadratic Volterra via $M$-mode RL kernel approximation ($H=0.1$, $N=252$, batch $5\,000$, GPU). $M = 5$ already saturates the kernel-fit error ($\approx 4\%$ relative) and gives the best IV-RMSE of the sweep, $7\times $ faster than the exact $O(N^2)$ baseline}{table.10}{}}
